Subject: [PATCH 2/2] fix(amortization): start schedule from origination to
 match past payments

get_loan_projection() was calling generate_schedule() without
origination_date, so the schedule started from today and past confirmed
payments were never matched by the engine's year-month lookup. Changed
to start from params.origination_date with params.original_principal
and params.term_months, matching the year-end service pattern.

Changes:
- amortization_engine.get_loan_projection: use origination_date,
  original_principal, and term_months; override monthly_payment for
  ARM loans using real principal from confirmed schedule rows
- loan.py dashboard: original/floor chart schedules start from
  origination with original_principal
- savings_dashboard_service: derive current balance and projections
  from schedule by date instead of by index offset
- debt_strategy._compute_real_principal: use original_principal and
  term_months for full payment replay
- Updated 2 tests whose expectations changed due to the schedule now
  containing full loan history from origination

